verse.lines:
{lang-eng}Grace! ’tis a charming sound,
Harmonious to the ear;
Heav’n with the echo shall resound,
And all the earth shall hear.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}’Twas grace that wrote my name
In life’s eternal book;
’Twas grace that gave me to the Lamb,
Who all my sorrows took.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Grace taught my wandering feet
To tread the pilgrim road;
And new supplies each hour I meet
While pressing on to God.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Grace taught my heart to pray,
And made my eyes o’erflow;
’Tis grace which kept me to this day,
And will not let me go.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Grace all the work shall crown
Through everlasting days;
It lays in love the topmost stone,
And well deserves the praise.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Oh, let that grace inspire
My heart with strength divine;
May all my powers to Thee aspire,
And all my days be Thine.{/lang-eng}
